Type the following command: dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/null. Change it froma  foreground to a background job
Answer: bg
Run this command 3 more times, but start it as a background job immeditely
Answer: dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/null &
Use jobs to get information about current background jobs
Answer: jobs
From top, change the niceness on one of the dd processes to -5 and observe what happens
Answer: top, press r and then specify -5
From top, send a sigkill signal to top and observe what happens
Answer: top, press k and then specify -9
Fom the command line, terminate all remaining dd processes
Answer: killall dd
